<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="679" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3848: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-26T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 26,
                                        1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>514. Your 958 [<hi rend="italic">858</hi>], February 13, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Secretary of War believes that notice through press, and letter of
                            Secretary to Senate and House Military Committees<note n="17" xml:id="d679fn17">See telegram to the Chargé in Russia, no. 507,
                                Feb. 24, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_617">p.
                                    617</ref>.</note> make unnecessary statement you propose.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>